ooh...

Bitchin'

Well, I went to kiss her on the forehead, you know. But it was *so* dark, I accidentally got her lips. I started to pull away, but then I felt her start to kiss me back. FOOTBALL!

Yeah look, about tomorrow, I... I've got a question for ya. I just found out that one of my groomsmen had had an emergency and can't make it.

(standing up too) M-Me-me-me!

Hi
Hey, can I talk to you about this groomsman thing? If you pick Ross, he'll walk you down the isle just fine. But if you choose me, you'll be getting some comedy!

Rachel gets a chair and sits opposite him) See, when I was a kid, I was always left out of everything, you know, and it really made me feel... insecure. You know, I was always picked last in gym. Even behind that big fat exchange student who didn't even know the rules to baseball. I mean, this guy would strike out and then run to third. Anyway, If I'm the only one left out of this wedding, I just know that all those feelings are gonna come rushing back.
All right fine, I pick you.
(Getting up and raising his fist in victory) Y-Y-YEEESSS! Make "groom" for Chandler.
(smiling to himself) Good. I'm just getting some coffee. So I'm alert for the wedding.
(smiling to himself too) That's what I was doing too.
(barely containing himself at this point) Well, you have fun tonight.
You too.
Oh, I will.
Me too.

Okay.

Oh!

Hey.

Honey.
I'm so sorry...
Everyone. Erica, baby!
Monica. Calm, self.

(To Chandler) We had a good time. By the way, I wanted to ask you something. It would really mean a lot to me, if the baby was a boy, that you name him after my father, Jiminy Billy Bob (Monica smiles at Chandler and his he looks shocked and scared, getting no support from his wife)

Pheebs!

Monica's grandmother.
Oh my God!
Relax! We just get her some antacids.
She doesn't have a stomach ache, she's in labor.
Oh my God!

All right, Chandler get the coats. Erica let's go. Phoebe and Joey, keep packing! Oh my God we're gonna have a baby. All right. We're gonna have a baby! OH MY GOD, WE'RE GONNA HAVE A BABY! Oh God, oh God, I got to sit down, I got to sit down. Ooh! (she's hyperventilating)
Honey, it's gonna be okay.
Chandler, wait, wait, wait...
What?
Oh my God!
Relax! We'll just get her some antacids.

Oh my God!
Breathe, breathe, breathe... Good.

To use the bathroom.

Wow!

How do you feel?

Okay!
Okay!

Bye!
Bye!
Okay.

Okay.
Okay.
I love you.
I love you.

Alright.

Okay.
